data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), the **sync-over-async bridge for the Cosmos DB provider is removed entirely**. The opt-in (`CosmosOptionsExtension.EnableSyncOverAsync()` or similar) no longer exists.

Every synchronous LINQ operator — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()` — and `SaveChanges()` will throw an **`InvalidOperationException`** at runtime.

## The Fix

Convert all synchronous calls to their async equivalents:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- This only affects the **Cosmos DB provider** — the relational providers still support sync operations.
- `Add()` remains synchronous (it's an in-memory operation on the change tracker).
- You'll need to propagate `async/await` up your call stack (controllers, services, etc.).
